", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.6188138127326965, "span": {"begin": 773, "end": 782}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000728"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "androgen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984222650527954, "span": {"begin": 796, "end": 804}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013734", "mim:300068"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "androgen related disorders", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9991273880004883, "span": {"begin": 873, "end": 899}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000728"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "androgen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9988068342208862, "span": {"begin": 873, "end": 881}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:367", "231", "2232"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AR", "obj": "gene", "prob": null, "span": {"begin": 911, "end": 913}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:367", "231", "2232"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AR", "obj": "gene", "prob": null, "span": {"begin": 962, "end": 964}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000740"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "anemias", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999960660934448, "span": {"begin": 1011, "end": 1018}}, {"id": ["mesh:D010024", "mim:166710"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "osteoporosis", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999977350234985, "span": {"begin": 1020, "end": 1032}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009133"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "muscle wasting", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999949336051941, "span": {"begin": 1034, "end": 1048}}, {"id": ["mesh:D011470"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "benign hyperplasia of the prostate", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999990463256836, "span": {"begin": 1053, "end": 1087}}], "text": "The activation of the AR is a generally recognized process and is supported by empirical evidence for AR agonists.   Testosterone propionate, 17-methyl testosterone and trenbolone were identified as agonists in the US EPA Androgen receptor pathway model, which integrates in vitro assays for receptor binding, coregulator recruitment and transactivation, and these stressors have also been shown to increase AR activation in Hershberger assay or other in vivo assays (Kleinstreuer et al., 2018; Browne et al., 2018).  Compounds that act as AR agonists have been used as positive controls in validation of OECD TG 458 and in validation studies by ICCVAM (OECD, 2023; ICCVAM, 2003). Compounds acting as AR agonists have been evaluated in ToxCast in vitro assays for AR (U.S. EPA, 2022).  Synthetic androgen ligands have been developed as potential drugs for the treatment of androgen related disorders; selective AR modulator are ligands acting as tissue-specific AR agonists and are being studied for effects on anemias, osteoporosis, muscle wasting and benign hyperplasia of the prostate but have not yet been approved for clinical use (Dalton &amp; Gao, 2010; Luetjens &amp; Weinbauer, 2012).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:14:38 +0000 2026"}